(42, 6, 47, 45, 2, 7, 10, 'doeth them', 'Connection of Obedience and Reward', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to teachings and the resulting consequences. Both passages emphasize that those who ''doeth'' good will receive glory and eternal life, while those who do not obey will face tribulation.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
