(42, 6, 49, 26, 33, 31, 31, 'heareth, and doeth not', 'Hearing and Doing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not just hearing words but also acting on them. Luke illustrates the consequences of failing to act, while Ezekiel describes people who hear but do not do. This connection highlights the theme of genuine obedience versus superficial acknowledgment.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 49, 59, 1, 22, 26, 'heareth, and doeth not', 'Connection of Hearing and Doing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not just hearing the word but also acting upon it. Luke describes the consequences of failing to build on a solid foundation, while James warns against being merely a hearer, highlighting the necessity of doing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 49, 40, 13, 20, 22, NULL, 'Foundation and Rootlessness', 'This connection highlights the theme of instability in faith. Both passages emphasize the consequences of a lack of depth, with the house without a foundation falling and the seed in stony places lacking root and becoming unfruitful.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 49, 40, 23, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Obedience and Action', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not just hearing but also doing. Luke highlights the consequences of failing to act, while Matthew warns against following those who do not practice what they preach.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 49, 61, 1, 5, 9, 'without a foundation', 'Foundation and Spiritual Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of building a strong foundation in faith and virtue. Luke 6:49 warns against a lack of foundation, while 2 Peter 1:5-9 encourages adding qualities to faith to ensure spiritual fruitfulness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 49, 62, 2, 3, 4, 'he that heareth, and doeth not', 'Obedience and Foundation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to God''s commandments as a foundation for true knowledge of Him. The failure to act on His words leads to ruin, paralleling the idea that claiming to know Him without keeping His commandments is deceitful.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 49, 20, 28, 18, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Uprightness and Foundation', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of one''s actions. Luke 6:49 illustrates the downfall of a house without a foundation, while Proverbs 28:18 states that the perverse shall fall. This connection highlights the importance of a solid moral foundation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 1, 40, 8, 5, 13, 'he entered into Capernaum', 'Jesus Enters Capernaum', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus entering Capernaum, which serves as the setting for the centurion''s request for healing. This connection highlights the significance of Capernaum as a location for Jesus'' ministry and miracles.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 1, 42, 7, 1, 10, 'he entered into Capernaum', 'Capernaum and Healing Connection', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' arrival in Capernaum, where he encounters the centurion''s servant in need of healing. Both passages emphasize the significance of faith and authority in the healing process.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 1, 40, 7, 28, 29, 'ended all his sayings', 'Authority in Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the conclusion of Jesus'' teachings, highlighting the impact on the audience. The astonishment of the people in Matthew reflects their recognition of his authority, which is implied in Luke''s account of his teachings in Capernaum.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 2, 1, 24, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Mercy and Truth', 'This connection highlights the themes of care and divine guidance. In both passages, there is an emphasis on the importance of mercy, as seen in the centurion''s concern for his servant and Abraham''s servant''s acknowledgment of God''s mercy.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 2, 12, 5, 2, 3, 'servant, who was dear unto him', 'Healing of Servants', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing through the intervention of a significant figure. In both passages, a servant is in a dire condition, prompting the centurion and the maid to seek help from a prophet or healer.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 2, 43, 4, 46, 47, 'ready to die', 'Healing of Sick Servants', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of healing for those ''at the point of death.'' The centurion''s servant and the nobleman''s son are both in critical condition, showcasing the theme of faith in Jesus'' healing power.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 2, 1, 24, 2, 14, 'dear unto him', 'Servanthood and Care', 'Both passages emphasize the deep bond between a master and his servant. In Luke, the centurion''s servant is dear to him, while in Genesis, Abraham''s servant is entrusted with a significant task, showcasing loyalty and care.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 2, 18, 31, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Suffering and Integrity', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering and the moral integrity of individuals. In both passages, there is an emphasis on the condition of a servant and the character of the person involved, suggesting a deeper exploration of loyalty and righteousness in times of distress.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 2, 20, 29, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Servanthood and Care', 'This connection highlights the theme of care for servants. In both passages, the relationship between a master and his servant is emphasized, showcasing the importance of nurturing and valuing those in one''s service.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 2, 40, 27, 54, 54, 'centurion', 'Centurion''s Recognition of Authority', 'This connection highlights the centurion''s role in both passages, showcasing his authority and recognition of Jesus'' divine nature. In Luke, the centurion''s concern for his servant reflects his compassion, while in Matthew, he acknowledges Jesus as the Son of God after witnessing miraculous events.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 3, 40, 8, 5, 5, 'beseeching him', 'Centurion''s Request for Healing', 'Both passages emphasize a centurion seeking healing for a servant. The act of beseeching Jesus connects the two accounts, illustrating the faith and urgency of the centurion''s request.', 'parallel', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
